============================================================
PHASE 10 OBJECTIVE
============================================================

Build the commercial SaaS and enterprise packaging layer for zDash.

Main goals:

1. Add billing plan system
2. Add subscription lifecycle model
3. Add usage metering
4. Add feature entitlement system
5. Add quota enforcement
6. Add invoice/payment provider adapter interface
7. Add Stripe-compatible billing adapter shell
8. Add mock billing adapter for local development
9. Add plugin marketplace system
10. Add plugin installation/enable/disable workflow
11. Add enterprise license model
12. Add white-label branding system
13. Add customer onboarding flow
14. Add enterprise admin console
15. Add SaaS pricing/plan frontend pages
16. Add usage dashboard
17. Add tenant billing dashboard
18. Add marketplace UI
19. Add enterprise export/import packaging
20. Add tests for billing, marketplace, entitlements, quotas, and branding

IMPORTANT SAFETY RULES:
- Do not enable live trading by default.
- Do not enable real IoT actions by default.
- Do not enable real social posting by default.
- Do not bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Do not bypass content approval checks.
- Do not bypass tenant isolation.
- Do not hardcode payment provider secrets.
- Do not store raw credit card data.
- Do not implement custom card processing.
- Payment provider integration must use tokenized provider references only.
- Mock billing must be the default in development.
- Real billing must require explicit provider config.
- Usage quotas must fail safely.
- Enterprise license must not weaken production safety locks.

